channel.title: Text on the labboards
channel.description:
Hello, guys! I am from Ukraine and we love this great game so much! We are doing translation to our language but it is some troubles. We translated many of audio voices, text and textures. But some text on textures of boards in the labs is still incomprehensible. So I decided to ask you for help, because it is your native language. Please write the exact text that is written here on textures. This text is written by hand and me it very difficult to recognize:'( Sorry for my bad english, i speak russian.
There is the link with that textures: [url]https://yadi.sk/d/re2ZmLdGFZhgH[/url]
Some text that I was trying to recognize (is it right recognized?):
[COLOR='Orange']c0a1x_labboard_am1.png "Paul - can you call Dr J. O. Marcel on ext 1187.463 about the Niobium 5 - He needs it for that AI Project 'thing' - thanks - Dr Montero"
[COLOR='Orange']c0a1x_labboard_am2_00_00_00.png Sample Specimen 'EP - 0021' ------------------> Purity - NMR spectragraphs display a 31.965% exotic content, 6.313% unknown contamination (SR 3.96:A13) and 61.722% (?normal?) chemical composition.
Sample exhibits variable (?EMR?) polarisation suggesting specimen is a di-electric medium with internal charged particle systems. Chereneou? phenomena? has bar? exhibited in both samples from er-00 range and er-01 range 'greens'
New specimen has been (?requisitioned?) IO:- GG-3883 Non standard analysis Requested. Thanks -Dr Truman
=======================================================
Partial conformity with constancy (?of?) interfacial angles. Exotic matter with odd physical properties possible reasons for abnormal growth structure.
Exhibits both trigonal and monoclinic axis orientation.
[COLOR='orange']c0a1x_labboard_am3.png Theorised resonance frequences and associated matter refraction of polarized di-electric medium EP-0021
1.Observed "2p" energy spikes form within plasmatic shards converting negative mass exotic matter into displaced plasmatic particle streamers. This seems to occur more in lower purity samples (621% Em). Unknown how physical structure affects this.."
2. String based theory non-viable are to potential time dilation (?effects?). (??????), highly (?ame?) forms of specimen (?C?????) form strings (?r????) than ????? refractions (?ove?) to (?higher?) resonance levels
NMR spectragraph of EP-0021
[i]The words "(?xxx?)" (????? etc) i cant recognize.[/i]
I really hope for your help!

item.title: Text on the labboards
item.dc:creator: Kenley
item.description:
am1:
That’s all correct.

am2_00_00_00:
First paragraph all correct.

Second paragraph all correct except “Cherenkov phenomena has been exhibited”

The rest is all correct.

am3:
“Theorized resonance frequencies”

  1. All correct

  2. “String based theory non-viable due to potential time dilation effects.
    However, highly pure forms of specimen could form strings other
    than helix refractions due to higher resonance levels.”

Hope that helps! Good luck with your translation project!
